<tr><td valign=top colspan=5><table border=0 width="100%"><tr><td><font size="+1"><B><a name="2075">Screwy</a></B> / IPD No. <a class="linkid"  href="machine.cgi?id=2075">2075</a> <I>/ June, 1932 / 1 Player</I></font><br>&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=top></td></tr></table></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=top align=right><b>Average Fun Rating: </b></td><td colspan=4 width="80%" align=left valign=top><font color=red>No ratings on file</font> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[ <a href="rate/login.pl?gid=2075" target="do_a_rating">Be first to rate this game!</a> ]
</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Manufacturer: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><span title="Click here to perform a search for all pinball games manufactured by 'Bally'"><a href="search.pl?searchtype=advanced&amp;mfgid=47">Bally Manufacturing Corporation (1931-1983) <i>[Trade Name: Bally</i>]</a></span></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Date Of Manufacture: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>June, 1932</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Type: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Pure Mechanical (PM)&nbsp;<a href="showhelp.pl?item=type&amp;highlight=PM#PM" title="Show Type Classifications" target="help"><img alt="[?]" style="cursor: help;" src="/graphic/question.gif" border=0></a></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" align="right" valign=baseline><b>Serial Number Database:</b></td><td colspan=4 align="left" valign=baseline><a href="redirect.pl?http://www.ipsnd.net/View.aspx?id=2075">View at <I>The Internet Pinball Serial Number Database</I> (IPSND.net)</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size="-1"><I>(External site)</i></font></td></tr><tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Specialty: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Table Top/Counter Game&nbsp;<a href="glossary.php#Table_Top/Counter_Game" title="Explain this specialty" target="help"><img alt="[?]" style="cursor: help;" src="/graphic/question.gif" border=0></a><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notable Features: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>7 balls for 1 cent, or 10 balls for 5 cents. "Figure 8" <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Playfield">playfield</a> layout. <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Cabinet">Cabinet</a> advertised as 30 inches long, 15 1/2 inches wide, 7 inches high in front, 9 inches high in back, and weighs 30 lbs.</td></tr>
<tr><td width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Design by: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><span title="Click here to perform a search for all pinball games that 'Raymond&nbsp;T.&nbsp;Moloney' was connected with."><a href="search.pl?searchtype=advanced&amp;ppl=Raymond%20T.%20Moloney">Raymond&nbsp;T.&nbsp;Moloney</a></span></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notes: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>In the game examples presented to us, the <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Playfield">playfield</a> 'glass' has been glass, or thick plastic.<br><br>Bally offered this game for $16.50 with an optional wood stand for $2.50 or metal stand for $2.00.<P></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" align=right valign=baseline><b>Photos in: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>
Automatic Age, Jun 1932, pages 176-177<br>
The Billboard, 07-16-1932<br>
<a href="redirect.pl?http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1889933023/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=1889933023&linkCode=as2&tag=theinternetpi-20&linkId=Z72T2JLDLWNKE4TA">Encyclopedia of Pinball Volume 2</a>, page 135<br>
</td></tr>
